            <content:encoded><![CDATA[https://kotaku.com/ac-shadows-how-level-up-fast-make-money-atomfall-skills-1851773102<br/><br/><div id="readability-page-1" class="page"><div><div><figure id="" data-id="58bd008f3eb1f3ca775850b171b4e12e" data-recommend-id="image://58bd008f3eb1f3ca775850b171b4e12e" data-format="jpg" data-width="1280" data-height="720" data-lightbox="false" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="false" data-imagerights="in-house-art" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->Ubisoft / Kotaku<!-- -->, <!-- -->Ubisoft / Kotaku<!-- -->, <!-- -->Ubisoft / Kotaku<!-- -->, <!-- -->Capcom / Kotaku<!-- -->, <!-- -->Ubisoft / Kotaku<!-- -->, <!-- -->SenseGames<!-- -->, <!-- -->Ubisoft / Kotaku<!-- -->, <!-- -->Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Rebellion<!-- -->, <!-- -->Rebellion<!-- -->, <!-- -->Rebellion</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="58bd008f3eb1f3ca775850b171b4e12e" data-recommend-id="image://58bd008f3eb1f3ca775850b171b4e12e" data-format="jpg" data-width="1280" data-height="720" data-lightbox="false" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>Whether you want to know how to use <em>Assassin’s Creed Shadows</em>’ level scaling to your advantage, get rich quick in feudal Japan, or make your hideout as pretty as it can be, we’ve got the tips for you this week. In addition to that, we’ll also help you get started in <em>Atomfall </em>and tell you what to expect out of <em>AI Limit</em>, so read on.</p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="fba5e4c55840d624bda341a0eb76c135" data-recommend-id="image://fba5e4c55840d624bda341a0eb76c135" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A screenshot of Assassin’s Creed Shadows. Naoe is on top of a building, looking out at a vast mountainous autumn landscape." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="A screenshot of Assassin’s Creed Shadows. Naoe is on top of a building, looking out at a vast mountainous autumn landscape." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->Ubisoft / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="fba5e4c55840d624bda341a0eb76c135" data-recommend-id="image://fba5e4c55840d624bda341a0eb76c135" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A screenshot of Assassin’s Creed Shadows. Naoe is on top of a building, looking out at a vast mountainous autumn landscape." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p><em>Assassin’s Creed Shadows </em>is an open-world RPG through and through, complete with stats to level up and progressively more powerful gear to find. As you might expect, it employs a level scaling system, where the enemies and quests you encounter get stronger as you do. That is to say, if you’re level five, the enemies around you will be level five. When you reach level six, the enemies will turn into level six enemies. Easy, right? - Timothy Monbleau <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/assassins-creed-shadows-level-scaling-legendary-gear-1851771943&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/assassins-creed-shadows-level-scaling-legendary-gear-1851771943">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="1f82632b75e9cafd38d50152860db6e9" data-recommend-id="image://1f82632b75e9cafd38d50152860db6e9" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A screenshot from Assassin’s Creed Shadows. A digitally fragmented silhouette of a person is standing in a dark landscape in front of two cherry blossom trees." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="A screenshot from Assassin’s Creed Shadows. A digitally fragmented silhouette of a person is standing in a dark landscape in front of two cherry blossom trees." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->Ubisoft / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="1f82632b75e9cafd38d50152860db6e9" data-recommend-id="image://1f82632b75e9cafd38d50152860db6e9" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A screenshot from Assassin’s Creed Shadows. A digitally fragmented silhouette of a person is standing in a dark landscape in front of two cherry blossom trees." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>You’d be entirely forgiven for thinking that the Projects screen in <em>Assassin’s Creed Shadows</em> is just a Battle Pass system. The gradual drip feed of rewards presented in a straight line evokes strong déjà vu of countless live service and free-to-play games like <em>Fortnite </em>or <em>Genshin Impact</em>. Additionally, <em>Assassin’s Creed Shadows </em>has microtransactions, so you might (reasonably) fear that Projects exist just to separate your cash from your wallet. Fortunately, while Projects are similar to Battle Passes in form, they differ a bit in function. - Timothy Monbleau <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/assassins-creed-shadows-projects-reset-time-battle-pass-1851771958&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/assassins-creed-shadows-projects-reset-time-battle-pass-1851771958">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="db6ec0c27cdd599b353a22e9c39d02c5" data-recommend-id="image://db6ec0c27cdd599b353a22e9c39d02c5" data-format="jpg" data-width="1440" data-height="810" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A one-on-one duel with Yasuke in a burning castle in Assassin’s Creed Shadows." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="A one-on-one duel with Yasuke in a burning castle in Assassin’s Creed Shadows." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->Ubisoft / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="db6ec0c27cdd599b353a22e9c39d02c5" data-recommend-id="image://db6ec0c27cdd599b353a22e9c39d02c5" data-format="jpg" data-width="1440" data-height="810" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A one-on-one duel with Yasuke in a burning castle in Assassin’s Creed Shadows." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>While it’s completely viable to cut down your foes solely via stealthy assassinations and brute-force katana strikes as either Naoe or Yasuke, leveling up and investing in additional abilities makes combat far more enticing. You can Spartan kick your enemies as Yasuke and lurch forward in a lightning-quick strike as Naoe. But such skills require you to spend time earning XP to invest Mastery Points. But how can you do so in the most efficient, and quickest, ways? - Brandon Morgan <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/assassins-creed-shadows-level-up-contracts-castle-tera-1851771996&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/assassins-creed-shadows-level-up-contracts-castle-tera-1851771996">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="3ae3806905f261c8cc8fb6d023f57e3d" data-recommend-id="image://3ae3806905f261c8cc8fb6d023f57e3d" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A female NPC in Monster Hunter Wilds looks past the camera." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="A female NPC in Monster Hunter Wilds looks past the camera." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->Capcom / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="3ae3806905f261c8cc8fb6d023f57e3d" data-recommend-id="image://3ae3806905f261c8cc8fb6d023f57e3d" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A female NPC in Monster Hunter Wilds looks past the camera." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>I’ve heard tales of people willingly and happily spending an hour or two—sometimes even three or more—in a game’s character creator. Folks craft celebrity lookalikes, themselves, and their ideal vision of the perfect hero. Personally, I’m in and out in five minutes, ready to play. But what happens if you speed through that process with your character and then find it’s subpar in gameplay? Fortunately, <em>Monster Hunter Wilds</em> won’t shoulder you with buyer’s remorse given its various settings for tweaking your character’s style. - Brandon Morgan <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/monster-hunter-wilds-appearance-cosmetics-transmog-1851772498&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/monster-hunter-wilds-appearance-cosmetics-transmog-1851772498">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="e8130c88d90daf8727a6c2f7f51ae23d" data-recommend-id="image://e8130c88d90daf8727a6c2f7f51ae23d" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Yasuke stands on a dock while wearing fancy armor. Ships set sail behind him." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Yasuke stands on a dock while wearing fancy armor. Ships set sail behind him." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->Ubisoft / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="e8130c88d90daf8727a6c2f7f51ae23d" data-recommend-id="image://e8130c88d90daf8727a6c2f7f51ae23d" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Yasuke stands on a dock while wearing fancy armor. Ships set sail behind him." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>When I first discovered the ornament vendor in <em>Assassin’s Creed Shadows</em>—the kindly woman selling decorations and <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/assassins-creed-shadows-hideout-customization-unlock-1851772163&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/assassins-creed-shadows-hideout-customization-unlock-1851772163">customization options for the hideout</a></span>—I had a feeling I’d end up spending tons of Mon decking out my dojo. Well, that assumption was correct. Many thousands of Mon later, I was rolling in rocks, trees, and roofing materials. But I was out of money. So I had to find some new strats to keep the cash flowing. - Brandon Morgan <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/assassins-creed-shadows-mon-treasure-valuables-settsu-1851772640&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/assassins-creed-shadows-mon-treasure-valuables-settsu-1851772640">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="866c7eb80e2dcd0c6a70aa5d125f28e7" data-recommend-id="image://866c7eb80e2dcd0c6a70aa5d125f28e7" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="An image of a character in a robe holding a staff while kneeling on their knees in a dark tunnel." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="An image of a character in a robe holding a staff while kneeling on their knees in a dark tunnel." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="false" data-imagerights="other-license" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->SenseGames</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="866c7eb80e2dcd0c6a70aa5d125f28e7" data-recommend-id="image://866c7eb80e2dcd0c6a70aa5d125f28e7" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="An image of a character in a robe holding a staff while kneeling on their knees in a dark tunnel." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>There is an abundance of soulslike titles these days, giving fans of the brutal genre plenty of options for where to spend their time exploring, making builds, and taking down extremely challenging bosses. If you’re an anime enthusiast as well, you may have had your eye on <em>AI Limit</em>, which costs only $35. This may leave you wondering how long of a journey the game offers and whether it’s worth investing in. So let’s get into it. - Billy Givens <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/ai-limit-soulslike-how-long-to-beat-short-hard-1851772663&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/ai-limit-soulslike-how-long-to-beat-short-hard-1851772663">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="787c2d7c9c9dc569201c48426890b5df" data-recommend-id="image://787c2d7c9c9dc569201c48426890b5df" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Promotional art for Atomfall shows a person with an assault rifle looking out over a storm." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Promotional art for Atomfall shows a person with an assault rifle looking out over a storm." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="false" data-imagerights="other-license" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Rebellion</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="787c2d7c9c9dc569201c48426890b5df" data-recommend-id="image://787c2d7c9c9dc569201c48426890b5df" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Promotional art for Atomfall shows a person with an assault rifle looking out over a storm." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>To level your skills up in <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;External link&quot;,&quot;https://cdkeys.pxf.io/c/379647/1566025/18216?subId1=KT&amp;u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cdkeys.com%2Fatomfall-pc-steam&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://cdkeys.pxf.io/c/379647/1566025/18216?subId1=KT&amp;u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cdkeys.com%2Fatomfall-pc-steam" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><em>Atomfall</em></a></span>, you’ll need to find Training Stimulants. And while you’ll have a solid selection of skills you can buy early on, you can add additional skills to your repertoire by finding manuals out in the world. But which to choose first?  - Billy Givens <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/atomfall-skills-training-stimulant-fortitude-weapon-thr-1851772475&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/atomfall-skills-training-stimulant-fortitude-weapon-thr-1851772475">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="44fb6822de2e0cd9ff1708e433eb743e" data-recommend-id="image://44fb6822de2e0cd9ff1708e433eb743e" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A man walks toward the camera while wielding an assault rifle." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="A man walks toward the camera while wielding an assault rifle." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="false" data-imagerights="other-license" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Rebellion</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="44fb6822de2e0cd9ff1708e433eb743e" data-recommend-id="image://44fb6822de2e0cd9ff1708e433eb743e" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A man walks toward the camera while wielding an assault rifle." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>There have been quite a few games over the years that examine the fallout of a nuclear event, but developer Rebellion’s new title <em>Atomfall</em> distinguishes itself by using a real-life accident as the basis for its tale. Taking place in an alternate reality following the Windscale nuclear disaster of 1957, this UK-based survival-action experience provides a large open-world experience with plenty to do and see in a radioactive England. Here’s how long it’ll take you to see what <em>Atomfall</em> has to offer. - Billy Givens <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/atomfall-how-long-to-beat-finish-trophy-achievement-1851772231&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/atomfall-how-long-to-beat-finish-trophy-achievement-1851772231">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="1371d44a3a870da3ea7fd496daa62bc1" data-recommend-id="image://1371d44a3a870da3ea7fd496daa62bc1" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Yasuke standing before the main hideout entrance in Assassin’s Creed Shadows." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Yasuke standing before the main hideout entrance in Assassin’s Creed Shadows." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->Ubisoft / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="1371d44a3a870da3ea7fd496daa62bc1" data-recommend-id="image://1371d44a3a870da3ea7fd496daa62bc1" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Yasuke standing before the main hideout entrance in Assassin’s Creed Shadows." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>Customization is one of my favorite parts of just about any video game, followed closely by base-building elements. <em>Assassin’s Creed Shadows</em> features both, and you can even customize your base—otherwise known as your hideout—with cherry blossom trees, deer statues, intricate pathways, and so much more. Unfortunately, it’ll cost you. Who knew interior and exterior decorating would be such a lucrative market in Feudal Japan?! - Brandon Morgan <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/assassins-creed-shadows-hideout-customization-unlock-1851772163&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/assassins-creed-shadows-hideout-customization-unlock-1851772163">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="1c9c037afd49eb6488857fc259d4426a" data-recommend-id="image://1c9c037afd49eb6488857fc259d4426a" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="An abaonded telephone booth sits in an irradiated wasteland." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="An abaonded telephone booth sits in an irradiated wasteland." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="false" data-imagerights="other-license" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Rebellion</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="1c9c037afd49eb6488857fc259d4426a" data-recommend-id="image://1c9c037afd49eb6488857fc259d4426a" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="An abaonded telephone booth sits in an irradiated wasteland." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>If you’re just diving into <em>Atomfall</em>, you should know this survival title is designed to test your skills and patience (in a good way). With danger lurking around every corner and extremely limited resources at your disposal, you’ll want to approach every moment with caution and planning. Before you set off on your journey in <em>Atomfall</em>, here are three tips to keep in mind that can help improve your chances at survival. - Billy Givens <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/atomfall-survival-stealth-fighting-difficulty-training-1851772235&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/atomfall-survival-stealth-fighting-difficulty-training-1851772235">Read More</a></span></p></div></div></div>]]></content:encoded>
